task.summary: renamed project from grunt-contrib-ember to grunt-ember-templates
bumped to v0.4.2rc5; updated dependencies to be compatible with grunt 0.4.0rc5

v0.4.2rc7 - upgraded for grunt 0.4.0rc7 and handlebars 1.0.rc.2
/hattip @GManzato

Reduce dependencies to just ember-template-compiler.js.
Updates to the latest ember / handlebars (1.0.0-rc.3).
Update readme to reflect grunt 0.4 compatible release
v0.4.7: Deprecate `ember_templates` task in favor of `emberTemplates`.
Update getting started section in README

Fixup and test AMD option.
AMD option now wraps entire output file, instead of individual templates. Also, tests were added for the AMD option.
Add `templateBasePath` alias to `templateBaseDir`. Default `templateFileExtensions` now also include `.hjs`.
Minor tweaks related to new `precompile` option
Remove unnecessary new line from amd output

Rename `generateRegistrationJs` -> `templateRegistration`
Simplified implementation of `templateRegistration` to accept a single template's name and content as args. Also, clarified relationship of this option to the `amd` option in the README.
Provide example of `templateRegistration` that registers templates as modules
Simplify file pattern matching test so that preprocess test doesn't need a custom extension
Add `preprocess` to README. Bump to v0.4.16.
Tightening of var declarations and initialization
Updated docs for templateCompilerPath and handlebarsPath
